  "body": "I was trying to use the TestUtils onMouseEnter and onMouseLeave events, like,\n\n```\nit('should trigger mouse events', () => {\n        let renderedButton = TestUtils.renderIntoDocument(<someButton/>);\n        TestUtils.Simulate.mouseEnter(renderedButton.getDOMNode());\n        TestUtils.Simulate.mouseLeave(renderedButton.getDOMNode());\n});\n```\n\nI had no luck with either of the Simulates' mouse events.\nHowever, i found on stackoverflow a workaround to use this,\n\n```\n it('should trigger mouse events', () => {\n    let renderedButton = TestUtils.renderIntoDocument(<someButton/>);\n    TestUtils.SimulateNative.mouseOver(renderedButton.getDOMNode());\n    TestUtils.SimulateNative.mouseOut(renderedButton.getDOMNode());\n});\n```\n\nand this works for now and i also haven't noticed an open issue about this, hence opening one here.  Is there already a fix for it or should I keep using this workaround? I just feel iffy about using SimulateNatives events as opposed to Simulate which works for most of the other click events we have in our app.\n",
